Four identical squares and one rectangle are placed together to form one large square as shown. The length of the rectangle is how many times as large as its width?\\

\begin{asy}
import olympiad;
import cse5;
defaultpen(white);
size(100);
unitsize(8mm);
defaultpen(linewidth(.8pt));

draw(scale(4)*unitsquare);
draw((0,3)--(4,3));
draw((1,3)--(1,4));
draw((2,3)--(2,4));
draw((3,3)--(3,4));
\end{asy}
\\
$ \textbf{(A)}\ \frac {5}{4} \qquad \textbf{(B)}\ \frac {4}{3} \qquad \textbf{(C)}\ \frac {3}{2} \qquad \textbf{(D)}\ 2 \qquad \textbf{(E)}\ 3$
